			<content name="Parts">
				<title>JRebirth Parts</title>

				<item>Application, GlobalFacade, Notifier</item>
				<item level="1">JRebirth Core Classes</item>
				<item>CommandFacade &amp; Commands</item>
				<item level="1">Manage reusable tasks</item>
				<item>ServiceFacade &amp; Services</item>
				<item level="1">Perform your long tasks</item>
				<item>UiFacade &amp; Models [View [, Controller]]</item>
				<item level="1">Display your User Interface</item>
				<item>Wave</item>
				<item level="1">Allow Component communicating among them</item>
				<item>BehaviorFacade &amp; Behaviors</item>
				<item level="1">Extend several components by using a common Behavior</item>

			</content>

			<content name="Components">

				<title>JRebirth Components</title>

				<item>3 kinds of Component:</item>
				<item level="1">Command</item>
				<item level="1">Service</item>
				<item level="1">Model</item>
				<item>Easy to build &amp; bind</item>
				<item>Can communicate asynchronously</item>
				<item>Loosely coupled, avoid memory leak</item>
				<item>Interact thanks to convenient methods:</item>
				<item level="1">callCommand</item>
				<item level="1">returnData</item>
				<item level="1">attachUi</item>
			</content>
			
			<content name="Links">

				<title>Components Links</title>

				<item>A Component is never constructed manually</item>
				<item level="1">They are injected or picked</item>
				<item>A Component Type can have several instances</item>
				<item level="1">Identified by a UniqueKey</item>
				<item level="2">that can be string(s)</item>
				<item level="2">or Object(s) using methods annotated by @KeyGenerator</item>
				<item>Injection</item>
				<item level="1">@LinkComponent and @LinkInnerComponent</item>
				<item level="1">Be careful, strong references can generate memory leak</item>
				<item>Picking</item>
				<item level="1">getModel(...), getCommand(...), getService(...)</item>
				<item level="1">Get the component when you need it</item>
				<item level="1">Allow to dispose it after usage</item>
			</content>

			<content name="Threads">
				<title>JRebirth Threads</title>

				<item>JAT</item>
				<item level="1">JavaFX Application Thread</item>
				<item></item>
				<item>JIT</item>
				<item level="1">JRebirth Internal Thread</item>
				<item level="1">Used to manage Waves and Subscriptions</item>
				<item></item>
				<item>JTP &amp; HPTP</item>
				<item level="1">JRebirth Thread Pool and High Priority Thread Pool</item>
				<item level="1">Used to run long tasks</item>
			</content>

		</slide>

		<slide showAnimation="ScaleFromMax" hideAnimation="FadeOut">

			<title>Command Layer</title>

			<content name="Overview">
				<title>Principle</title>
				<item>Commands are JRebirth Components</item>
				<item></item>
				<item>Reusable</item>
				<item>... and disposable</item>
				<item></item>
				<item>Can be Stateless (by defaults)</item>
				<item>... or Stateful (according to your usage)</item>
			</content>

			<content name="Command Type">
				<title>Type</title>

				<item>There are 2 command types:</item>
				<item></item>
				<item>SimpleCommand</item>
				<item level="1">Run atomically</item>
				<item></item>
				<item>MultiCommand</item>
				<item level="1">Can run several commands sequentially</item>
				<item level="1">Can run several commands in parallel</item>
			</content>

			<content name="Runnable">
				<title>How to run</title>

				<item>Each command can be run in </item>
				<item>a dedicated Thread:</item>
				<item level="1">Into JAT to update the UI</item>
				<item level="1">Into JIT to do some custom tasks related to JRebirth</item>
				<item level="1">Into JTP to do all long tasks</item>
				<item></item>
				<item>Running Thread is chosen according to:</item>
				<item level="1">Command Class Hierarchy</item>
				<item level="1">@RunInto annotation used</item>
			</content>

